HEADWORD: Cornea
<hw>Cor"ne*a</hw> <pr>(k?r"n?-?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Corneas</plw> <pr>(-<?/z)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Fem. sing., fr. L.
<ets>corneus</ets> horny, fr. <ets>cornu</ets> a horn. See
<er>Horn</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The transparent part of
the coat of the eyeball which covers the iris and pupil and admits light
to the interior. See <er>Eye</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

